						<div class="postbody">The drive only uses IRQ while data is being loaded. It's stopped doing that before the code is even run. (After loading I could unplug the FDSStick and reset, doesn't change anything.) Though, you could put an additional test in that waits around and counts any spurious IRQs; I don't believe this is the case though.<br /><br />All I would suggest is that something done in tests 4-10 is affecting the state of success for test 3. A state that's &quot;random on power up&quot;.</div>

