						<div class="postbody">Will suggest one thing: in your IRQ routine you SEI and CLI? Why?<br />SEI is already implied/forced by the IRQ itself, and RTI will clobber the interrupt flag.<br /><br />If there is a second IRQ here that $4030 does not ack, the CLI will end up retriggering it in an infinite loop?<br /><br />Maybe relevant is this curious note about a delay in the BIOS after a disk IRQ ack?<br /><div class="quotetitle"><a href="https://nesdev.com/FDS%20technical%20reference.txt" class="postlink">FDS technical reference.txt</a> wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">;disk IRQ acknowledge routine ([$0101] = 10xxxxxx).<br />;don't know what this is used for, or why a delay is put here.<br />$E1EF	PHA<br />$E1F0	LDA $4030<br />$E1F3	JSR Delay131<br />$E1F6	PLA<br />$E1F7	RTI<br /></div></div>

